and legacy projects), including [[Generator (computer programming)|generators]], [[coroutines]], the finally keyword, list in foreach, [[namespace]]s, [[Closure (computer science)|closures]], [[Trait (computer programming)|traits]] and short array syntax. It includes a full-fledged [[SQL]] editor with editable query results.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eweek.com/c/a/Application-Development/JetBrains-PhpStorm-50-Provides-New-Framework-Support-560166/|title=JetBrains PhpStorm 5.0 Provides New PHP Framework Support|author=Darryl K. Taft|date=2012-09-13|publisher=[[Eweek]]|accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drdobbs.com/tools/jetbrains-phpstorm-50-aligns-to-symfony2/240007578|title=JetBrains PhpStorm 5.0 Aligns To Symfony2 and Yii|author=Adrian Bridgwater|date=2012-09-18|publisher=Dr.Dobbs|accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref>\n\nPhpStorm is written in [[Java (programming language)|Java]]. Users can extend the IDE by installing plugins created for PhpStorm or write their own plugins. The software also communicates with external sources like XDebug.\n\nAll features available in [[WebStorm]] are included in PhpStorm,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://devnet.jetbrains.com/message/5456233;jsessionid=111D786511C0F8006447972E46AE73EA#5456233 |title=PhpStorm vs WebStorm}}</ref> which adds support for PHP and databases.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/ |title=PhpStorm |quote=PhpStorm includes all the functionality of WebStorm (HTML/CSS Editor, JavaScript Editor) and adds full-fledged support for PHP and Databases/SQL. |accessdate=2013-04-21}}</ref> WebStorm ships with pre-installed JavaScript plugins (such as for [[Node.js]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://confluence.jetbrains.com/display/PhpStorm/PhpStorm+FAQ |title=Which IDE do I need? |work=PhpStorm FAQ |accessdate=2013-04-21}}</ref>\n\n==Key features==\n[[File:JetBrainsPhpStormDebugging.png|thumb|right|Zero-configuration web application debugging with [[Xdebug]] in PhpStorm. Darcula color scheme]]\n[[File:JetBrainsPhpStormVCSExample.png|thumb|right|[[Version Control|Version Control Systems]] Integration]]\n[[File:JetBrainsPhpStormDataSource.png|thumb|right|Viewing Data Source Structure and other SQL and Databases related features in PhpStorm]]\n\n===PHP editor===\n*PhpStorm provides a rich [[code editor]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://phpmaster.com/phpstorm-review-and-give-away/|title=PhpStorm&nbsp;\u2013 Review and Give Away|author=Bruno Skvorc|date=2012-08-13|publisher=PHP Master|accessdate=2017-06-06}}</ref> for PHP with [[syntax highlighting]], extended code formatting configuration, on-the-fly error checking, and [[code completion]].\n*PHP 5.3, 5.4, 5.5, 5.6, 7.0, 7.1, 7.2 support, including [[Generator (computer programming)|generators]], [[coroutines]], the finally keyword, list in foreach, using empty() on the result of function calls and other expressions, [[Trait (computer programming)|traits]], [[Closure (computer science)|closures]], class member access on instantiation, short array syntax, array [[dereferencing]] on function call, binary literals, expressions in static calls, it supports return types and scalar type hints and constant visibility, etc. It can be used for both modern and legacy PHP-based projects.\n*[[Code completion|Code autocompletion]] finalizes classes, methods, variable names, and PHP keywords, plus commonly used names for fields and variables depending on their type.\n*[[Coding style]] Support ([https://www.specbee.com/blogs/introduction-php-standard-recommendation-psr PSR1/PSR2], Drupal,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.specbee.com/blogs/php-debugging-how-debug-your-php-code-drupal-debugging-techniques-included|title=Debugging techniques for Drupal|author= Harika |date=September 3, 2019}}</ref> Symfony, Zend).\n*[[PHPDoc]] support. The IDE provides code completion suggestions based on @property, @method and @var annotations.\n*Duplicated Code Detector.\n*PHP Code Sniffer (phpcs) that checks for [[code smell]]s on the fly.\n*[[Refactoring]]s (Rename, Introduce Variable, Introduce Constant, Introduce Field, Inline Variable, Move Static Member, Extract Interface).\n*[[Smarty (template engine)|Smarty]] and [[Twig (template engine)|Twig]] templates editing (Syntax errors highlighting; Smarty functions and attributes completion; automatic insertion of paired braces, quotes and closing tags; and more).\n*[[Model\u2013view\u2013controller|MVC]] view for [[Symfony]], and [[Yii]] [[Web application framework|frameworks]].\n*PHAR support.\n\n===Development environment===\n*[[SQL]] and [[databases]] support (live database schema refactoring, generation of [[schema migration]] scripts, export query result to file or clipboard, editing of stored procedures, etc.).\n*Remote [[System deployment|deployment]] over [[FTP]], [[SSH File Transfer Protocol|SFTP]], [[FTPS]] etc. with automatic synchronization.\n*[[Version control systems]] integration ([[Git (software)|Git]] (including specific [[GitHub]] features), [[Subversion (software)|Subversion]], [[Mercurial]], [[Perforce]], [[Concurrent Versions System|CVS]], [[Team Foundation Server|TFS]]) allowing you to perform actions ([[Commit (data management)|commit]], [[Merge (revision control)|merge]], [[diff]], etc.) right from the IDE.\n*Local History (tracks any changes in the code locally).\n*PHP [[Unified Modeling Language|UML]] (UML class diagrams for PHP code with refactorings invoked right from the diagram).\n*Phing support (autocompletion, checks standard tags, properties, target names, path attribute values in build files).\n*[[Issue tracking system|Issue tracker integration]].\n*Support for [[Vagrant (software)|Vagrant]] and [[Docker (software)|Docker]], [[Secure Shell|SSH]] console & remote tools\n*[[Google App Engine]] for [[PHP]] Support\n\n===Debugging and testing===\n*Easy-to-configure visual debugger ([[Xdebug]], Zend Debugger)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.phpdeveloper.org/news/22684|title=Gary Hockin: Debugging PHP Command Line (with PHPStorm and XDebug)|author=Chris Cornutt|date=2015-05-07|publisher=PHPDeveloper.org|accessdate=2015-10-12}}</ref> for inspecting context-relevant local variables and user-defined watches, including arrays and complex objects, and editing values on the fly.\n*Scripts can be [[Profiling (computer programming)|profiled]] right from PhpStorm with either XDebug or Zend Debugger. An aggregated report is available, and the user can jump from the execution statistics directly to the function in PHP code.\n*[[PHPUnit]] tests can be developed in PhpStorm and run instantly from a directory, file or class using the context menu options) with code coverage.\n\n===JavaScript, CSS and HTML features===\n*Code completion for JavaScript, HTML and CSS (for tags, keywords, labels, variables, parameters and functions).\n*[[HTML5]] support.\n*Live Edit: changes in the code can be immediately viewed in the browser without reloading the page.\n*[[CSS]]/[[Sass (stylesheet language)|SASS/SCSS]]/[[LESS (stylesheet language)|LESS]] support (code completion, error highlighting, validation, etc.).\n*[[Zen Coding]].\n*Code navigation and usages search (Go to declaration/symbol, Find Usages).\n*[[ECMAScript]] Harmony Support.\n*JavaScript refactoring (Rename, Extract Variable/Function, Inline Variable/Function, Move/Copy, Safe delete, Extract embedded script into file).\n*JavaScript [[debugger]] and [[unit testing]].\n\n==Licensing and updates policy==\nIn November 2015 JetBrains switched to licensing PhpStorm on a subscription basis. Annual subscriptions or monthly subscriptions maintained for 12 consecutive months also receive a \"perpetual fallback license\" to the major version available at the time of purchase. PhpStorm is available for individual developers, and business and organizations. Additional discounted and complementary licenses are available for startups, students and teachers, and non-commercial open source projects. These complementary licenses require approval and do not include the perpetual fallback clause, i.e. they expire.\n\n==See also==\n*[[JetBrains]]\n*[[Comparison of integrated development environments#PHP|Comparison of integrated development environments]]\n*[[PHP_Development_Tools|PHP Development Tools (PDT)]]\n*[[Eclipse_(software)|Eclipse IDE]]\n*[[Xdebug]]\n*[[Komodo Edit]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n*[http://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/documentation/index.html Docs and Demo]\n*[http://confluence.jetbrains.com/display/PhpStorm/Tutorials PhpStorm Tutorials]\n\n{{PHP}}\n{{JavaScript}}\n{{Integrated development environments}}\n\n[[Category:Integrated development environments]]\n[[Category:PHP]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{advert|date=June 2016}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2015}}\n}}\n{{Infobox software\n| name = JetBrains PhpStorm\n| logo = Phpstorm.png\n| screenshot = JetBrainsPhpStormScreenshot.png\n| caption = \n| developer = [[JetBrains|JetBrains s.r.o.]]\n| released = {{Start date and age|2009}}\n| latest release version = 2019.3\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2019|11|28}}<ref>{{cite web |title=PhpStorm 2019.3 is released|url=https://blog.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/2019/11/phpstorm-2019-3-release/ |website=blog.jetbrains.com |accessdate=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n| programming language = [[Java (programming language)|Java]]\n| operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]], [[Linux]]\n| language = English\n| genre = [[Integrated development environment]]\n| license = [[Commercial software|Commercial]] [[proprietary software]]\n| website = {{URL|https://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/}}\n}}\n\n'''PhpStorm''' is a commercial, cross-platform [[Integrated development environment|IDE]]  (integrated development environment) for [[PHP]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/248117/slick_phpstorm_makes_editing_javascript_and_php_fun.html|title=Slick PhpStorm Makes Editing JavaScript and PHP Fun|author=Erez Zukerman|date=2012-01-12|publisher=[[PCWorld]]|access